quran[21]{c,v,t,f}:
  100,10,"And that within the breasts is obtained,[1]","[1] i.e., when all secrets are made known."
  100,11,"Indeed, their Lord with them, that Day, is [fully] Aware.[1]","[1] Fully acquainted and familiar with everything about each one of them."
  101,1,"The Striking Calamity -",""
  101,2,"What is the Striking Calamity?",""
  101,3,"And what can make you know what is the Striking Calamity?",""
  101,4,"It is the Day when people will be like moths, dispersed,[1]","[1] The people will be as such after having been expelled from their graves."
  101,5,"And the mountains will be like wool, fluffed up.[1]","[1] i.e., beginning to disintegrate."
  101,6,"Then as for one whose scales are heavy [with good deeds],",""
  101,7,"He will be in a pleasant life.",""
  101,8,"But as for one whose scales are light,",""
  101,9,"His refuge[1] will be an abyss.[2]","[1] Literally, \"mother\" (a man's original refuge) , which will envelop him as in an embrace.\n[2] i.e., the pit of Hellfire."
  101,10,"And what can make you know what that is?",""
  101,11,"It is a Fire, intensely hot.",""
  102,1,"Competition in [worldly] increase diverts you",""
  102,2,"Until you visit the graveyards.[1]","[1] i.e., remain in them temporarily, meaning until the Day of Resurrection."
  102,3,"No! You are going to know.",""
  102,4,"Then, no! You are going to know.",""
  102,5,"No! If you only knew with knowledge of certainty...[1]","[1] The conclusion of this verse is estimated to be \"...you would not have been distracted from preparing for the Hereafter.\""
  102,6,"You will surely see the Hellfire.",""
  102,7,"Then you will surely see it with the eye of certainty.[1]","[1] i.e., with actual eyesight."
  102,8,"Then you will surely be asked that Day about pleasure.[1]","[1] i.e., the comforts of worldly life and whether you were grateful to AllƒÅh for His blessings."
